    "Their inception score is 3.45, 7.8% higher than the previously announced StackGan, outperforming the state-of-the-art models.Wu et al.",
    "created the Gaussian-Poisson Generative Adversarial Network GP-GAN [28] to combine the strengths of gradient-based approaches with GANs.",
    "It's the first GAN study on high-resolution image mixing.",
    "They use Gaussian-Poisson Equation to describe the high-resolution picture blending problem, a joint optimization bound by gradient and colour information.",
    "Gradient filters give gradient information, inspired by past work."
